# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Backend .dockerignore
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Applies to the `./backend` build context used by both the API and the
# Worker Dockerfiles. Keeping the context lean speeds up `docker build`
# (less data to send to the daemon) and prevents host-only artefacts from
# being baked into intermediate image layers.

# Build outputs and intermediate artefacts — must be rebuilt inside the image
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/out/
**/publish/
**/artifacts/

# Test source — production images do not ship tests. The test .csproj
# files ARE intentionally kept in context because the solution-level
# `dotnet restore DocuPilot.sln` walks every project listed in the .sln
# (omitting them would fail the restore step). Only the test source code
# and assets are excluded.
tests/**/*.cs
tests/**/appsettings*.json
tests/**/xunit.runner.json

# IDE / editor noise
**/*.user
**/*.suo
**/.vs/
**/.vscode/
**/.idea/

# Logs and temp files
**/*.log
**/[Ll]ogs/
**/TestResults/

# OS noise
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/desktop.ini

# Documentation lives outside the runtime image
**/*.md

# Secrets / local config that must never enter an image
**/*.env
**/*.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/*.pfx
**/*.key
**/secrets.json
**/appsettings.*.Local.json
**/appsettings.Production.json

# Defensive — the build context is `./backend`, so .git wouldn't be picked
# up anyway, but listed for clarity.
**/.git/
**/.gitignore
